content.description: Its entire body has evolved into a highly efficient radiator, gifting it with astounding stamina. When someone has mounted it, this Pal takes caution not to burn them.

partnerSkill.name: Red Hare
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Applies Fire damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

content.name: Pyrin Noct
content.description: It burns mysterious dark matter as energy and expels the remaining particles from its body. If someone rides it, they should take care so as not to gallop down the path of darkness.

partnerSkill.name: Black Hare
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Applies Dark damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

content.name: Elphidran
content.description: It possesses a demeanor as pure as its appearance suggests. Perhaps because of this, it is sometimes unable to discern good from evil, often allowing wrongdoers to take advantage of it.

partnerSkill.name: Amicable Holy Dragon
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. While fighting together, Dark Pals drop more items when defeated.

content.name: Elphidran Aqua
content.description: It possesses a demeanor as pure as its appearance suggests. Perhaps because of this, it harbors no ill will in any of its actions and is indifferent even after killing someone.

partnerSkill.name: Amicable Water Dragon
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. While fighting together, Fire Pals drop more items when defeated.

content.name: Woolipop
content.description: Its entire body is 18,000 times sweeter than sugar. Carnivorous Pals lured by its scent will find themselves overwhelmed by sweetness and even pass out should they take a bite of this Pal.

partnerSkill.name: Candy Pop
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes drops Cotton Candy when assigned to MonsterFarm.

content.name: Cryolinx
content.description: It can easily climb steep mountains with its hard claws. However, its short legs make it difficult to descend, often leaving it stranded in high places.

partnerSkill.name: Dragon Hunter
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, Dragon Pals drop more items when defeated.

content.name: Melpaca
content.description: Don't be fooled by this Pal's fluffy appearance. A hypersonic kick from one of its long legs may send you flying to the other side of the world.

partnerSkill.name: Pacapaca Wool
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Sometimes drops Wool when assigned to MonsterFarm.

content.name: Surfent
content.description: Its hydrodynamic form is well suited to life in water. Poachers often catch them and use them in place of surfboards.

partnerSkill.name: Swift Swimmer
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden to travel on water. While mounted, prevents stamina depletion while moving over water.

content.name: Surfent Terra
content.description: Its aerodynamic form is well suited to life on the sand. Poachers often catch them and use them in place of surfboards.

partnerSkill.name: Sand Swimmer
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden.

content.name: Cawgnito
content.description: Long ago it freely soared the skies. After losing a contest with Galeclaw, it abandoned the skies, and now lives a secretive life in the dark of night.

partnerSkill.name: Telepeck
partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Unique_DarkCrow_TelePoke.

content.name: Azurobe
content.description: This Pal's white ribbon turns black if doused with impure water. Given its usefulness in detecting poison, this Pal was once overhunted. This past has left them bitter towards humanity.

partnerSkill.name: Waterwing Dance
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden to travel on water. Applies Water damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

content.name: Cattiva
content.description: At a glance it appears full of confidence, but it is in fact weak and cowardly. Being toyed with by a Cattiva is in many ways the greatest of disgraces.

partnerSkill.name: Cat Helper
partnerSkill.description: While in team, Cattiva helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.

content.name: Depresso
content.description: It has few friends because of the perpetually grouchy look on its face, but it is in fact kindhearted. Some have seen it feeding Vixywho have strayed from their pack.

partnerSkill.name: Caffeine Inoculation
partnerSkill.description: When activated, Depresso drinks a massive amount of energy drinks, causing its movement speed to increase.

content.name: Fenglope
content.description: In ages past, its beautiful visage was a common sight in paintings. As time passed, its beautiful pelt and antlers were often seen in works of art.

partnerSkill.name: Wind and Clouds
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can double jump while mounted.

content.name: Reptyro
content.description: Magma-like blood runs throughout its body. If a large amount of water is thrown on it, this water rapidly heats, causing an immense vapor explosion.

partnerSkill.name: Ore-loving Beast
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Improves efficiency of mining ores while mounted.

content.name: Ice Reptyro
content.description: Ice cold blood runs throughout its body. If heated rapidly, its blood evaporates, causing an immense vapor explosion.

partnerSkill.name: Ice-loving Beast
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Improves efficiency of mining ores while mounted.

content.name: Maraith
content.description: It relishes the peculiar scent living things give off when they are near death. If a Maraith has taken a liking to you, it is safe to assume that is why.

partnerSkill.name: Messenger of Death
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Applies Dark damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

content.name: Robinquill
content.description: A pal that is very similar to humans who hunt and live in the forests. It may prove to be a key for understanding what Pals are and how they diverged from humans so long ago.

partnerSkill.name: Hawk Eye
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, allows you to deal more damage to weak points.

content.name: Robinquill Terra
content.description: A Pal that lives a hunting life in rocky areas and is very close to humans. When Robinquill Terra bones are found in ruins, there are always human bones found nearby as well.

partnerSkill.name: Hawk Eye
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, allows you to deal more damage to weak points.

content.name: Relaxaurus
content.description: Contrary to its blasé appearance, it's quite ferocious. It perceives everything in its sight as prey and will stop at nothing to devour it.

partnerSkill.name: Hungry Missile
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can rapidly fire a missile launcher while mounted.

content.name: Relaxaurus Lux
content.description: One day, Relaxaurus had an idea. Maybe it was about time for a change. Just then, an electric shock raced through its body!

partnerSkill.name: Missile Party
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can rapidly fire a missile launcher while mounted.

content.name: Kitsun
content.description: Despite its appearance, Kitsun is extremely sensitive and will flee into a cave when spooked. Long ago, it was considered an ill omen if one were found nearby.

partnerSkill.name: Clear Mind
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Unaffected by the cold or heat while riding this Pal.

content.name: Leezpunk
content.description: A Pal that always takes great care to maintain a stylish stance. Always on the hunt for the coolest poses, if given a mirror it will spend all day posing in front of it.

partnerSkill.name: Sixth Sense
partnerSkill.description: When activated, utilizes its sixth sense to detect nearby dungeons.

content.name: Leezpunk Ignis
content.description: A Pal that has an unusual obsession with their standing posture. Always in search of the hottest pose, this Pal's owner is constantly presented with fervent stances.

partnerSkill.name: Sixth Sense
partnerSkill.description: When activated, utilizes its sixth sense to detect nearby dungeons.

content.name: Fuack
content.description: Using its own body water, this Pal can create waves anywhere. It body surfs when in a hurry, but the resulting speed often ends in a fatal collision.

partnerSkill.name: Surfing Slam
partnerSkill.description: When activated, Fuack body surfs towards an enemy and slams into them.

content.name: Vanwyrm
content.description: The melodies of a flute made from the exoskeleton of a Vanwyrm are said to cross whole mountain ranges. In ages past, such flutes were used to signal an attack.

partnerSkill.name: Aerial Marauder
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Increases damage player deals to enemy weak points while mounted.

content.name: Vanwyrm Cryst
content.description: The melodies of a flute made from the exoskeleton of a Vanwyrm Cryst are said to cross whole mountain ranges. In ages past, such flutes were used to signal victory in battle.

partnerSkill.name: Aerial Marauder
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Increases damage player deals to enemy weak points while mounted.

content.name: Chikipi
content.description: Extremely weak and far too delicious. It is one of the weakest Pals alongside Lamball. No matter how many are hunted, they just keep appearing.

partnerSkill.name: Egg Layer
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes lays an Egg when assigned to MonsterFarm.

content.name: Dinossom
content.description: A Pal who once angered cannot be pacified. It rages on and on like an inferno. The phrase |step on a Dinossom's tail| has come to mean enraging someone.

partnerSkill.name: Fragrant Dragon
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Enhances Leaf attacks while mounted.

content.name: Dinossom Lux
content.description: Though struck by lightning, it lives on. The phrase |struck by a Dinossom Lux's bolt| has come to mean narrowly escaping death.

partnerSkill.name: Thunder Dragon
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Enhances Electricity attacks while mounted.

content.name: Sparkit
content.description: During the dry season, this Pal is always on the verge of blowing a fuse. Sparks can fly with even the slightest provocation, even amongst allies.

partnerSkill.name: Static Electricity
partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Electricity Pals.

content.name: Frostallion
content.description: Guardian deity of Palpagos Island, known as the Winter Caller. In the past, when a calamity struck the land, it soared into the sky and sealed away the threat by casting the island into an eternal winter.

partnerSkill.name: Ice Steed
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Changes the player's attack type to Ice and enhances Ice attacks while mounted.

content.name: Frostallion Noct
content.description: Guardian deity of Palpagos Island known as the Night Caller. In the past, when a calamity struck the land, it soared into the sky and sealed away the threat by casting the island into eternal darkness.

partnerSkill.name: Black Steed
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Changes the player's attack type to Dark and enhances Dark attacks while mounted.

content.name: Mammorest
content.description: The vegetation on its back varies between individuals. There is a long history of appreciating this veritable garden of a Pal, and there are even Mammorest pruning specialists.

partnerSkill.name: Gaia Crusher
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Improves efficiency of cutting trees and mining ores while mounted.

content.name: Mammorest Cryst
content.description: The vegetation on its back varies from individual to individual. There was a time when seeds of presumed extinct plants were found still frozen on the back of a Mammorest Cryst.

partnerSkill.name: Ice Crusher
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Improves efficiency of cutting trees and mining ores while mounted.

content.name: Felbat
content.description: Attacking from the shadows, this Pal traps its prey within its cloak-like wings. It's probably best not to know what happens within them, or why the inside of its wings are stained red.

partnerSkill.name: Life Steal
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, grants the player and Felbat the life steal effect which absorbs some of the received damage and restores HP.

content.name: Broncherry
content.description: Its scent drastically changes before and after pairing. It exudes a pleasing aroma after finding a partner, which is called the |fragrance of first love.|

partnerSkill.name: Overaffectionate
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Broncherry helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.

content.name: Broncherry Aqua
content.description: Its scent drastically changes before and after pairing. It exudes a pleasing aroma before finding a partner, which is called the |perfume of purity.|

partnerSkill.name: Overaffectionate
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Broncherry Aqua helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.

content.name: Faleris
content.description: When it finds its prey it unleashes a whirlwind of flames, burning the entire area to ash. Faleris breath is known for its pleasing scent.

partnerSkill.name: Scorching Predator
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. While fighting together, Ice Pals drop more items when defeated.

content.name: Blazamut
content.description: Legends say it was born during a volcanic eruption. A strange group even claims that this continent is laid upon the back of a giant Blazamut.

partnerSkill.name: Magma Kaiser
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Enhances Fire attacks while mounted.

content.name: Caprity
content.description: The shrub on this Pal's back produces berries as long as it is properly fed. It offers these berries to potential mates, and if the flavor is to their liking, romance blossoms.

partnerSkill.name: Berry Picker
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes drops Red Berries from its back when assigned to MonsterFarm.

content.name: Reindrix
content.description: Its transparent cerulean antlers glow with the cold of absolute zero. Any who touch them with their bare hands are instantly frozen over and smashed to pieces.

partnerSkill.name: Cool Body
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Keeps the rider cool in hot environments.

content.name: Shadowbeak
content.description: Born from the depths of insanity, its very existence should not be. Having lost all genetic ties to other Pals, one wonders if it could still even be considered a Pal.

partnerSkill.name: Modified DNA
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Enhances Dark attacks while mounted.

content.name: Sibelyx
content.description: A Pal that likes the rain, and will often bask in rain showers until the weather clears up. On rainy days, Foxparks can often be found taking shelter beneath it.

partnerSkill.name: Silk Maker
partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful IcicleThrow. Sometimes produces High Quality Cloth when assigned to MonsterFarm.

content.name: Vixy
content.description: The idol of Palpagos Island. If you bully a Vixy, you best be prepared to become enemies with the whole world.

partnerSkill.name: Dig Here!
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes digs up items from the ground when assigned to MonsterFarm.

content.name: Wixen
content.description: With the power of light, it produces arcane phenomena. It prefers to eat food well-done and is particularly hostile towards Katress.

partnerSkill.name: Lord Fox
partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, applies Fire damage to the player's attacks.

content.name: Lovander
content.description: Seeking a night of love, it is always chasing someone around. At first it only showed interest in other Pals, but in recent years even humans have become the target of its debauchery.

partnerSkill.name: Heart Drain
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, grants the player and Lovander the life steal effect which absorbs some of the received damage and restores HP.

content.name: Hoocrates
content.description: Often lost in thought, it sometimes finds it difficult to sleep. |I think, therefore I am.|

partnerSkill.name: Dark Knowledge
partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Dark Pals.

content.name: Kelpsea
content.description: Its personality changes depending on the quality of the water it was born into. Kelpsea born into polluted waters are generally ill-tempered and quickly become delinquents.

partnerSkill.name: Aqua Spout
partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Water Pals.

content.name: Kelpsea Ignis
content.description: Their personalities change depending on the temperature of the water where they were born. Kelpsea born in warm waters generally have a passionate, motivated personality.

partnerSkill.name: Lava Spout
partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Fire Pals.

content.name: Killamari
content.description: It wraps itself around an enemy's head, sucking out their insides. Pal mummies are occasionally found, but these are in fact Killamari victims.

partnerSkill.name: Fried Squid
partnerSkill.description: While in team, can be summoned and used instead of a glider. Can float for long periods of time while gliding.

content.name: Mozzarina
content.description: Milk pours from this Pal like water from an open faucet, regardless of its gender. It's truly a mystery of life, although this mystery may be better left unsolved.

partnerSkill.name: Milk Maker
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes produces Milk when assigned to MonsterFarm.

content.name: Wumpo
content.description: Researchers once tried to shave off its hair to reveal its true form. In the end, only hair was left, as if that was all there was to begin with.

partnerSkill.name: Guardian of the Snowy Mountain
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Wumpo helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.

content.name: Wumpo Botan
content.description: Researchers once tried to cut the grass off its body to reveal its true form. In the end, only grass was left, as if that was all there was to begin with.

partnerSkill.name: Guardian of the Grassy Fields
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Wumpo Botan helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.

content.name: Vaelet
content.description: The castle was filled with the king's favorite flowers. A great battle ensued, and flames approached the castle. Amidst the chaos, the spirit of a flower appeared.  - From the fairy tale, |The King's Flower.|

partnerSkill.name: Purification of Gaia
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, Earth Pals drop more items when defeated.

content.name: Nitewing
content.description: It carries newborn Pals to its nest and raises them as a surrogate parent. Once the baby Pal has fattened up, it hunts them.

partnerSkill.name: Travel Companion
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount.

content.name: Flopie
content.description: It prefers places that have an abundance of vegetation, but hay fever has apparently become a problem for Flopie as of late.

partnerSkill.name: Helper Bunny
partnerSkill.description: While in team, appears near the player. Automatically picks up nearby items.

content.name: Lyleen
content.description: A docile Pal full of love. It watches over small Pals who have lost their parents. It uses a full-power SolarBeam to discipline naughty Pals.

partnerSkill.name: Harvest Goddess
partnerSkill.description: When activated, the queen's soothing graces greatly restore the player's HP.

content.name: Lyleen Noct
content.description: An elegant Pal full of grace. It admonishes any who are disrespectful with a painful slap. Some Pals actively seek out this punishment.

partnerSkill.name: Goddess of the Tranquil Light
partnerSkill.description: When activated, the queen's soothing graces greatly restore the player's HP.

content.name: Elizabee
content.description: A chosen queen to rule over Beegardes. There is a never ending stream of servants willing to work themselves to death for the pleasure of serving their queen.

partnerSkill.name: Queen Bee Command
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, stats will increase the more Beegarde are in your team.

content.name: Beegarde
content.description: A servant that pledges loyalty to Elizabee. Any that cause harm to the queen are immediately expelled from the hive. It will gladly give its life to protect its queen.

partnerSkill.name: Worker Bee
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes drops Honey when assigned to MonsterFarm. While in team, Elizabee's stats will be increased.

content.name: Tombat
content.description: Often appears out of the blue to flaunt its prized wings in front of other Pals. Although this appears to be an intimidation tactic,  the Pal seems to derive some kind of pleasure from the display.

partnerSkill.name: Ultrasonic Sensor
partnerSkill.description: When activated, uses ultrasonic waves to detect the location of nearby Pals.

content.name: Mossanda
content.description: A Pal so powerful it's hard to believe. In one experiment, this Pal tore through 3,000 sheets of paper at once! It's only by some miracle that this Pal isn't a meat-eater.

partnerSkill.name: Grenadier Panda
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can rapidly fire a grenade launcher while mounted.

content.name: Mossanda Lux
content.description: A Pal whose power is truly shocking. By altering the electrical currents in its body, this Pal's been able to overload its own strength. When it comes to sheer power, this Pal may be top of the list.

partnerSkill.name: Grenadier Panda
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can rapidly fire a grenade launcher while mounted.

content.name: Arsox
content.description: In ancient times, carnivorous Pals pursued them relentlessly. The absurd fury in the cries of Arsox transformed into a raging inferno, which has been passed on to this day.

partnerSkill.name: Warm Body
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Keeps the rider warm in cold environments.

content.name: Rayhound
content.description: At full speed, it could be mistaken for a bolt of lightning. If two Rayhounds collide, the sound is like that of a powerful thunderclap.

partnerSkill.name: Jumping Force
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can double jump while mounted.

content.name: Fuddler
content.description: Its large claws boast of diamond-like hardness. However, sharpening these claws consumes most of its energy, leading it to sometimes spending entire days doing nothing else.

partnerSkill.name: Ore Detector
partnerSkill.description: When activated, generates subtle vibrations to detect nearby ore.

content.name: Astegon
content.description: A savage beast born of the abyss. Thou shall not stand before the beast. Thou shall not heed the beast.

partnerSkill.name: Black Anklyosaur
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Increases damage dealt to ore while mounted.

content.name: Verdash
content.description: Land that Verdash has run across becomes extremely fertile, with thick vegetation growing there soon after. It will not run anywhere that herbicide has been used.

partnerSkill.name: Grassland Speedster
partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, increases player's movement speed and applies Leaf damage to the player's attacks.

content.name: Foxcicle
content.description: On nights when the aurora is visible, it looks up towards the sky and begins to howl a beautiful song. This does, however, leave it vulnerable to attacks from enemies.

partnerSkill.name: Aurora Guide
partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Ice Pals.

content.name: Jetragon
content.description: Watches over Palpagos Island from high above. When calamity returns to the land, the earth will split open, and the skies will burn. It is destined to strike down the calamity in a flash of total destruction.

partnerSkill.name: Aerial Missile
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Can rapidly fire a missile launcher while mounted.

content.name: Daedream
content.description: It puts those it is interested in to sleep and shows them an endless stream of happy dreams. Those who fall under its spell are never to wake until death takes them.

partnerSkill.name: Dream Chaser
partnerSkill.description: While in team, appears near the player. Follows up player attacks with magic bullets.

content.name: Tanzee
content.description: Long ago, this Pal used long objects like tree branches as weapons. After coming into contact with humans, however, it found something slightly more effective: guns.

partnerSkill.name: Cheery Rifle
partnerSkill.description: When activated, Tanzee will mercilessly fire an assault rifle at nearby enemies.

content.name: Blazehowl
content.description: While it prefers raw meat, it always ends up eating well-done meat. This is due to its blistering claws, which it uses as its weapon—it simply doesn't realize its prey gets burned to a crisp.

partnerSkill.name: Hellflame Lion
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While fighting together, Leaf Pals drop more items when defeated.

content.name: Blazehowl Noct
content.description: While it prefers raw meat, it always ends up eating tainted meat. This is due to its dark claws, which it uses as its weapon—it simply doesn't realize its prey gets cursed.

partnerSkill.name: Darkflame Lion
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While fighting together, Normal Pals drop more items when defeated.

content.name: Kingpaca
content.description: Melpaca serve this Pal. Contests between Kingpaca offer up their vassals as a wager. Those seen alone are losers of such contests.

partnerSkill.name: King of Muscles
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Kingpaca helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.

content.name: Ice Kingpaca
content.description: With a heart of ice, this Pal is terrible at expressing its emotions. A solitary individual is pitiable, seen as too clumsy in the eyes of a Melpaca.

partnerSkill.name: King of Muscles
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While in team, Ice Kingpaca helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.

content.name: Gumoss
content.description: A strange Pal with a body resembling tree sap. It gradually loses strength if it has nothing to cover its body with, eventually rotting away.

partnerSkill.name: Logging Assistance
partnerSkill.description: While in team, improves efficiency of cutting trees.

content.name: Gumoss (Flower)
content.description: A strange Pal with a body resembling tree sap. It gradually loses strength if it has nothing to cover its body with, eventually rotting away.

partnerSkill.name: Logging Assistance
partnerSkill.description: While in team, improves efficiency of cutting trees.

content.name: Swee
content.description: Crawling along the ground, it eats microscopic organic matter. After a while, it discharges any substances that provide no nutrition. By using it as a mop for cleaning, everyone wins!

partnerSkill.name: Fluffy
partnerSkill.description: While in team, Sweepa's stats will be increased.

content.name: Sweepa
content.description: While hibernating, a large number of Swee hide within its voluminous body hair. The most ever recorded is 101.

partnerSkill.name: King of Fluff
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. While fighting together, stats will increase the more Swee are in your team.

content.name: Katress
content.description: With the power of shadows, it produces arcane phenomena. It prefers to eat food raw and is particularly hostile towards Wixen.

partnerSkill.name: Grimoire Collector
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, Normal Pals drop more items when defeated.

content.name: Ribbuny
content.description: A Pal who's never without a bright smile. Occasionally, it gets its tentacles tied up in knots by Cattiva's pranks. During those moments, its expression changes into something altogether demonic.

partnerSkill.name: Skilled Fingers
partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Normal Pals. While at a base, increases work efficiency if working at WeaponFactory_Dirty_01.

content.name: Beakon
content.description: Some think it is a related species to Ragnahawk, but there is in fact no connection. Using its sharp beak, it descends on its prey in a quick motion that resembles a bolt of lightning.

partnerSkill.name: Thunderous
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Applies Electricity damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

content.name: Warsect
content.description: The ultra-hard armor surrounding its body is extremely strong and heat resistant. Even a napalm blast would hardly leave a scratch.

partnerSkill.name: Hard Armor
partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, increases player's defense and applies Fire damage to the player's attacks.

content.name: Paladius
content.description: Once one with Necromus. Its gleaming form is free of all negative emotions. However, a glimmer of hatred can still be seen deep within its eyes.

partnerSkill.name: Holy Knight of the Firmament
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can triple jump while mounted.

content.name: Nox
content.description: If you find Nox hair in your bedding, you should leave it where it lays and leave immediately. Picking it up is a one-way-ticket to a never ending night.

partnerSkill.name: Kuudere
partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, applies Dark damage to the player's attacks.

content.name: Penking
content.description: Surprisingly, it is unrelated to Pengullet. Ever wanting to be the center of attention, this Pal will strut its stuff for any onlookers.

partnerSkill.name: Brave Sailor
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, Fire Pals drop more items when defeated.

content.name: Chillet
content.description: It can curl up its body and roll around at extremely high speeds. Long ago, people would tie bags of milk to domesticated Chillet as they grazed to produce butter using this spinning force.

partnerSkill.name: Wriggling Weasel
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Applies Dragon damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

content.name: Quivern
content.description: Sleeping while cuddling a Quivern is said to be a heavenly experience, but there are some who have been crushed and sent to heaven by ones that toss and turn in their sleep.

partnerSkill.name: Sky Dragon's Affection
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Enhances Dragon attacks while mounted.

content.name: Helzephyr
content.description: It calls forth lightning from the depths of hell. One who dies from Helzephyr's inferno is sure to be sent to the underworld.

partnerSkill.name: Wings of Death
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Applies Dark damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

content.name: Ragnahawk
content.description: Some think it is a related species to Beakon, but there is in fact no connection. It mainly eats rocks, and after many long years its beak and head have hardened to accommodate this diet.

partnerSkill.name: Flame Wing
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as an flying mount. Applies Fire damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

content.name: Bushi
content.description: Its body becomes a blade upon death, to be taken up by the next generation. If someone other than a Bushi wields this blade, the soul within torments them until they are driven mad.

partnerSkill.name: Brandish Blade
partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Unique_Ronin_Iai.

content.name: Celaray
content.description: Riding the wind, this Pal travels where it pleases. Should it find a partner along the way, the encounter will mark its journey's end.

partnerSkill.name: Zephyr Glider
partnerSkill.description: While in team, can be summoned and used instead of a glider. Allows you to move quickly for long periods of time while gliding with this Pal.

content.name: Necromus
content.description: Once one with Paladius.  Its darkened form is the embodiment of negative emotions.  However, a glimmer of compassion can still be seen deep within its eyes.

partnerSkill.name: Dark Knight of the Abyss
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can double jump while mounted.

content.name: Petallia
content.description: A Pal that transforms into a massive plant when at the end of its life. Once every ten years, a beautiful flower blooms and a new Petallia is born.

partnerSkill.name: Blessing of the Flower Spirit
partnerSkill.description: When activated, uses medicinal flowers to restore the player's HP.

content.name: Grintale
content.description: Grintale's eyes light up the moment anyone enters its territory. This is no figure of speech—its eyes literally light up.

partnerSkill.name: Plump Body
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Enhances Normal attacks while mounted.

content.name: Cinnamoth
content.description: Sniffing its scales produces a feeling of unparalleled euphoria. There was some effort to further regulate this byproduct, but the Free Pal Alliance have vehemently opposed these measures, putting a stop to them.

partnerSkill.name: Mysterious Scales
partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with PoisonFog.

content.name: Menasting
content.description: Being made of pure energy, its insides are completely hollow. This Pal crams still-living prey into its hollow body, where it absorbs them. Hellish screams of pain can often be heard coming from inside this Pal.

partnerSkill.name: Steel Scorpion
partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, increases the player's defense and Electricity Pals drop more items when defeated.

content.name: Orserk
content.description: It sends electricity into its foes' wounds, roasting them from the inside out. Fights between Orserk end in the blink of an eye.

partnerSkill.name: Ferocious Thunder Dragon
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, Water Pals drop more items when defeated.

content.name: Cremis
content.description: Compared to Lamball, it has finer wool and a temperament more suited for domestication. However, it has historically always been kept as a pet. Cuteness is considered a virtue.

partnerSkill.name: Fluffy Wool
partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Normal Pals. Sometimes drops Wool when assigned to MonsterFarm.

content.name: Dumud
content.description: When too relaxed, its reaction time drastically declines. Even if it were sliced from head to tail, it probably wouldn't even realize that it should be dead until the next morning.

partnerSkill.name: Soil Improver
partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Earth Pals.

content.name: Flambelle
content.description: When it starts crying, this Pal produces magma in place of tears. The magma that pours out is absorbed back into its body, causing it to get hotter and hotter. The more it cries, the stronger it becomes.

partnerSkill.name: Magma Tears
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes produces Flame Organ when assigned to MonsterFarm.

content.name: Rooby
content.description: Wild Rooby surprisingly never get sick. Eating one piece of charcoal a day, made by burning a branch, is the secret to its eternal health.

partnerSkill.name: Tiny Spark
partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Fire Pals.
